1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO CAPITAL EXPENDITURES; REAUTHORIZING OR
3 REAPPROPRIATING BALANCES, EXPANDING OR CHANGING PURPOSES,
4 EXTENDING EXPENDITURE PERIODS AND CHANGING AGENCIES;
5 ESTABLISHING CONDITIONS FOR THE REVERSION OR TRANSFER OF
6 UNEXPENDED BALANCES OF APPROPRIATIONS MADE BY THE LEGISLATURE
7 IN PRIOR YEARS.
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
10 SECTION 1. SEVERANCE TAX BONDS--REAUTHORIZATION AND
11 REAPPROPRIATION OF PROCEEDS.--For a prior year severance tax
12 bond appropriation for a capital outlay project as provided
13 in this act, the legislature may reauthorize or reappropriate
14 the unexpended balance of the severance tax bond proceeds,
15 expand or change the project purpose, extend the expenditure
16 period, change the recipient agency or establish conditions
17 for the reversion or transfer of the unexpended balance due
18 to:
19 A. the inability of a project to use the proceeds
20 of the severance tax bonds for the purpose originally
21 authorized by law;
22 B. the completion of a project without the use of
23 the appropriated severance tax bond proceeds;
24 C. unanticipated delays in the need for or
25 expenditure of the severance tax bond proceeds for the HTRC/HB 332/a/woec
Page 1

1 purpose originally authorized by law; or
2 D. required compliance with the federal Internal
3 Revenue Code of 1986, as amended.
4 SECTION 2. SEVERANCE TAX BONDS--REVERSION OF
5 PROCEEDS.--
6 A. Except as otherwise provided in another section
7 of this act:
8 (1) the unexpended balance from the proceeds
9 of severance tax bonds issued for a project that has been
10 reauthorized in this act shall revert to the severance tax
11 bonding fund:
12 (a) at the end of the expenditure
13 period as set forth in this act, if the expenditure period is
14 changed in this act; or
15 (b) if the expenditure period is not
16 changed in this act, pursuant to the time frame set forth in
17 the law that originally authorized the severance tax bonds or
18 the time frame set forth in any law that has previously
19 reauthorized the expenditure of the proceeds, whichever is
20 later; and
21 (2) all remaining balances from the proceeds
22 of severance tax bonds issued for a project that has been
23 reauthorized in this act shall revert to the severance tax
24 bonding fund three months after the reversion date for the
25 unexpended balances. HTRC/HB 332/a/woec
Page 2

1 B. For the purpose of this section, "unexpended
2 balance" means the remainder of an appropriation after
3 reserving for unpaid costs and expenses covered by binding
4 written obligations to third parties.
5 SECTION 3. GENERAL FUND AND OTHER FUND APPROPRIATIONS--
6 REVERSIONS.--
7 A. Except as otherwise provided in another section
8 of this act:
9 (1) the unexpended balance of an
10 appropriation from the general fund or other state fund that
11 has been changed in this act shall revert:
12 (a) at the end of the expenditure
13 period as set forth in this act, if the expenditure period is
14 changed in this act; or
15 (b) if the expenditure period is not
16 changed in this act, pursuant to the time frame set forth in
17 the law in which the original appropriation was made or the
18 time frame set forth in any law that has previously changed
19 the appropriation, whichever is later; and
20 (2) all remaining balances of an
21 appropriation from the general fund or other state fund that
22 has been changed in this act shall revert three months after
23 the reversion date for the unexpended balance.
24 B. Except as provided in Subsection C of this
25 section, the balance of an appropriation made from the HTRC/HB 332/a/woec
Page 3

1 general fund or other state fund shall revert pursuant to
2 Subsection A of this section to the originating fund.
3 C. The balance of an appropriation made from the
4 general fund or other state fund to the Indian affairs
5 department or the aging and long-term services department for
6 a project located on lands of an Indian nation, tribe or
7 pueblo shall revert pursuant to Subsection A of this section
8 to the tribal infrastructure project fund.
9 D. For the purpose of this section, "unexpended
10 balance" means the remainder of an appropriation after
11 reserving for unpaid costs and expenses covered by binding
12 written obligations to third parties.
